          Our <strong>One More Year Syndrome calculator</strong> helps you make one of the most important decisions of your financial journey: when to stop accumulating and start living off your savings. Whether you are a Lean FIRE minimalist or a Fat FIRE aspirant, the psychological pull of "just one more year" affects everyone. This calculator replaces emotional decision-making with quantified trade-offs.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Why Choose This OMY Calculator?</h3>

        <p class="mb-4">
          Most FIRE calculators focus on the accumulation phase — how much you need and when you will get there. But once you arrive at your FIRE number, a new challenge emerges: <strong>knowing when to walk away</strong>. The One More Year syndrome calculator addresses this gap by quantifying the specific impact of working 1-5 extra years after hitting your number.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          Unlike generic retirement calculators, this tool focuses on <strong>marginal analysis</strong> — the incremental benefit of each additional year. It translates abstract portfolio growth into tangible outcomes: how many extra luxury vacations per year, how many more cars you could buy, and most importantly, how many hours of your life each upgrade costs. This <strong>time vs. money framework</strong> is the most honest way to evaluate the OMY decision.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          The calculator is particularly powerful for <strong>high-income professionals</strong> who save aggressively. For someone earning $200K+ and saving $80K+/year, the double compounding effect makes each extra year extremely lucrative financially. But the same math also shows that after a certain point, you are working for <strong>rapidly diminishing returns on happiness</strong> — extra vacations you may not even want, on a timeline where your health may not support them.
        </p>

        <h3 class="mb-3 text-lg font-semibold text-ink">Key Features of This OMY Syndrome Calculator</h3>

        <p class="mb-4">
          See your <strong>portfolio boost and perpetual income increase</strong> instantly as you adjust the "Extra Years to Work" slider. The calculator translates financial gains into <strong>lifestyle upgrades</strong> — showing exactly how many luxury international vacations or cars you can afford every year forever with the extra safe income. The <strong>time cost</strong> is presented equally prominently: the exact hours of healthy life you trade for those upgrades, so you can judge the exchange rate honestly.
        </p>

        <p class="mb-4">
          The <strong>30-year portfolio divergence chart</strong> visualizes the growing gap between retiring today vs. waiting. You can adjust your <strong>expected real return</strong> (0–12%) and <strong>safe withdrawal rate</strong> (2–6%) to test different market assumptions. The chart automatically updates when you switch between dark and light mode. All calculations are performed client-side — no data is sent to any server, and nothing is stored.
        </p>
